<%# The standalone Atlas export (v0.21) — ONE self-contained file, no server,
    no dependencies: open it in any browser. Rendered by `rake
    enliterator:atlas[FILE]` with the data embedded; record click-through is
    disabled (there is nothing to click through to). %>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Atlas — <%= @title %></title>
  <style>
    :root { --line: #1e293b; }
    body { margin: 0; background: #0b0f1a; color: #cbd5e1;
           font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif; }
    header.atlas-head { padding: 1rem 1.2rem .6rem; }
    header.atlas-head h1 { margin: 0; font-size: 1.15rem; color: #f1f5f9; }
    header.atlas-head p  { margin: .3rem 0 0; font-size: .85rem; color: #64748b; max-width: 70rem; }
    main { padding: 0 1.2rem 1.2rem; }
    footer.atlas-foot { padding: .6rem 1.2rem 1.2rem; font-size: .78rem; color: #475569; }
    .atlas-stage canvas { height: 80vh !important; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <header class="atlas-head">
    <h1>Atlas — <%= @title %></h1>
    <p>
      The enliterated collection, drawn. Records are nodes; claims that name things are typed
      edges; the edge types are the controlled vocabulary. Hover an edge for its provenance —
      who asserted it, when, at what confidence, and the audit verdict where one exists. Press
      replay to watch the collection learn.
    </p>
  </header>
  <main>
    <%= render "enliterator/atlas/viewer", atlas: @atlas, embedded: true %>
  </main>
  <footer class="atlas-foot">
    Prepared <%= Time.current.strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M") %> ·
    <%= @atlas[:meta][:records] %> records · <%= @atlas[:meta][:claims_considered] %> claims considered ·
    Enliterator (the collection, tended) — every edge carries its provenance.
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
